
/*
 * 1. The [get-value] slot retrieves the value of the node referenced by the expression `:x:@.arguments/*/action`. This means it searches for a child node named [action] under any node within the [.arguments] node and returns its value.
 * 
 * Use cases:
 * - Extracting the value of an [action] parameter from HTTP request arguments in an endpoint.
 * - Retrieving a user-specified action from a set of input parameters for further processing.
 * - Accessing the value of a specific argument in a dynamic slot or lambda function to determine the next step in execution.
 */
get-value:x:@.arguments/*/action
